1
00:00:16,916 --> 00:00:20,333
It's all starting to make sense.
Witch Baba works for you.

2
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,583
Give me that again.

3
00:00:23,666 --> 00:00:26,291
Witch Baba works for you.

4
00:00:26,958 --> 00:00:28,666
- We're in cahoots, are we?
- Aah!

5
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:30,875
You're an influencer, are you?
Make predictions, do you?

6
00:00:30,958 --> 00:00:34,083
I have evidence that you
and Witch Baba are working together!

7
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:41,916
Witch Baba used Bulgarian
to send an encrypted message to Wa Zai.

8
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,625
This is the translation.

9
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:49,333
Bit quiet now.

10
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:50,416
CHEN CHIA-JEN

11
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,125
WITCH BABA
WATCH NEW VIDEO NOW

12
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Mom?

13
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:02,208
Mom!

14
00:02:35,958 --> 00:02:38,583
Do you have to listen to it
while we're eating?

15
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:47,333
I said, do you have to listen and eat?

16
00:02:48,375 --> 00:02:49,833
It's live.

17
00:03:06,541 --> 00:03:07,916
<i>What did you fucking say?</i>

18
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,041
- Say it again. I dare you.
- Fuck you! Fucking bastard!

19
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:12,750
Keep going and I'll charge you
with insulting an officer.

20
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:15,041
- Mr. Jen!
- Mr. Jen, stop.

21
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:17,041
Fucking little bitch!

22
00:03:17,125 --> 00:03:18,625
Where are you going?

23
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:23,666
Did you hear me?
I'm asking you. Where are you going?

24
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:26,541
I already told you. I have a show.

25
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,583
That's really lame.

26
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:34,500
Singing to people
that you don't even know. What a waste.

27
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:36,083
That's my job.

28
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:37,500
Your job?

29
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:40,875
It'd be better to use your time studying.

30
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:44,208
Well, it's none of your business.

31
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:50,708
And have you totally forgotten
what day it is today?

32
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:55,291
It's Mom's birthday.
But you're still a loser.

33
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:56,416
Excuse me?

34
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:59,208
You're not going anywhere today.

35
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:01,666
- You stay here. Have some respect.
- What are you doing?

36
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:04,000
- Put this down.
- No! Give it back! Give it back!

37
00:04:04,083 --> 00:04:06,625
- No, I won't. You're not going anywhere.
- Are you crazy?

38
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:08,666
You're pathetic and self-righteous.

39
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:11,208
- How dare you? Say that again!
- You just lie there all day.

40
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:13,958
I said you're self-righteous.

41
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:16,416
You always talk about Mom,
but it's your fault!

42
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
You knew she was unwell for a long time,

43
00:04:20,083 --> 00:04:22,416
but you kept pretending
everything was okay!

44
00:04:25,916 --> 00:04:28,750
What are you doing? You're crazy!

45
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,625
Loser, hey?! You think I'm a loser?

46
00:04:30,708 --> 00:04:34,541
Fuck you! I wish <i>you </i>died!

47
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:36,916
Give me back my mom!

48
00:04:48,750 --> 00:04:51,666
This is none of your business.
Don't come near me.

49
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,541
- Here. Look…
- Get away from me.

50
00:05:30,166 --> 00:05:31,375
Hey, Yu-chieh!

51
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,541
Have you checked your phone?

52
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:29,083
WITCH BABA

53
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:35,291
<i>Hello, guys! I'm Witch Baba.</i>

54
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:36,500
Chiu-chiu?

55
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:41,000
<i>Yesterday, I predicted</i>
<i>that someone would die from drowning.</i>

56
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:43,416
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

57
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:47,416
<i>But now, it's time</i>
<i>for the next prediction.</i>

58
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:51,625
<i>Reversed Obelisk.</i>

59
00:06:51,708 --> 00:06:53,666
<i>Orient Express.</i>

60
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:55,916
<i>Reversed Amazonia.</i>

61
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:57,458
<i>In the future,</i>

62
00:06:59,291 --> 00:07:02,000
<i>someone will be stabbed to death.</i>

63
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:20,666
- Hello?
- <i>Hey. It's Hippo.</i>

64
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,458
<i>Hah. I remember now.</i>

65
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:26,458
<i>I think I know who made</i>
<i>the Illuminati Tarot unboxing video.</i>

66
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:27,541
Who?

67
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:36,958
Hey. What's up?

68
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:39,416
Seriously?

69
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:41,375
Huh?

70
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,916
Uh, Yo Tzu is coming.

71
00:07:48,458 --> 00:07:50,541
After I introduce you,
I'm free to go, right?

72
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,708
So long as you don't play any tricks.

73
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:04,750
- Is Little Egg here?
- She's upstairs.

74
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,125
YU-CHIEH

75
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:23,625
- What's up?
- Hey. Yo! Yo!

76
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:25,166
You're here!

77
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,500
- Hey! Cheers!
- Hey!

78
00:08:38,791 --> 00:08:41,000
Yo.

79
00:08:48,125 --> 00:08:49,208
Why is he here?

80
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:58,541
Let's get a Lemon Grandma,
caramel macchiato, apple pie…

81
00:08:58,625 --> 00:08:59,875
Hey! What do you guys want?

82
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:03,166
Oh! The chocolate platter
looks good. And the New York cheesecake.

83
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,125
- And also one blueberry.
- Ooh! Sounds good.

84
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:06,875
- Oh… Cinnamon roll?
- Mmm. Yeah.

85
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:08,875
What's an opera cake? Let's try it.

86
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,166
Yeah. Let's order it.

87
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,791
Oolong tea. And a rainbow cake.

88
00:09:12,875 --> 00:09:14,458
- Hey, do you want a pancake?
- Ooh, yeah.

89
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:17,333
- "Daifuku Honey Cream Pancake."
- Mmm! Delicious.

90
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:19,041
- Hey.
- Sounds good.

91
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:20,708
And a salad. I'm starving.

92
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:22,750
Hey. Are you done ordering?

93
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:25,666
Yeah. This cop
will pay for everything, right?

94
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:28,416
Hey, keep looking.
Anything else that looks good?

95
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,333
Okay. Great.

96
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:31,708
Okay. Let me read it all back to you.

97
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:32,791
TAKE MEDICINE

98
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:36,125
Opera cake, oolong tea,
New York cheesecake, blueberry cheesecake,

99
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:40,708
apple pie, caramel macchiato,
Lemon Grandma, cinnamon roll,

100
00:09:40,791 --> 00:09:44,833
chocolate platter, honey cream pancake,
one garden salad, a rainbow cake,

101
00:09:44,916 --> 00:09:46,583
and three pumpkin spice lattes.

102
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,708
- Yes! That's right. Thank you.
- Okay. Thank you.

103
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:50,000
- Yeah!
- Okay.

104
00:09:51,666 --> 00:09:53,041
So, tell me. These cards…

105
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:55,416
Hey. Is a drink enough for you?
You can have some of ours.

106
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,791
- Whereabouts did you find them? I…
- Is Wei Yen okay?

107
00:09:57,875 --> 00:09:59,833
- Hey, did you see the news about Wa Zai?
- But it's…

108
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:01,833
- Can you…
- Oh! Your friend is so annoying!

109
00:10:01,916 --> 00:10:02,916
Tell him to shut up.

110
00:10:06,208 --> 00:10:07,750
You ask her.

111
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,166
- Huh?
- Mm-hmm.

112
00:10:10,875 --> 00:10:12,708
Please just help.

113
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:14,750
Hilarious.

114
00:10:14,833 --> 00:10:16,750
Uh, are we playing Chinese whispers?

115
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,041
This guy!

116
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:22,041
- Miss, I need your cooperation.
- So annoying.

117
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:24,416
I'm not talking to a killer.

118
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,958
- Beg your pardon?
- I'm not talking to a killer cop.

119
00:10:29,041 --> 00:10:30,208
You want trouble?!

120
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:32,250
- Sure! Cuff me. Go on!
- Hey! Are you serious?

121
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:34,500
Fine! Obstruction of justice, all of you!

122
00:10:34,583 --> 00:10:37,291
- Go away!
- Stop filming, all of you! No filming!

123
00:10:37,375 --> 00:10:39,750
- Yo. Chill. Chill. That's enough.
- You're not my dad!

124
00:10:56,416 --> 00:10:57,625
You're not my dad!

125
00:11:03,416 --> 00:11:04,750
Hey.

126
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:07,458
- What are you… Are you okay?
- It's… it's nothing.

127
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,833
- Are you… Oh shit.
- Hey, are you okay?

128
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:12,000
- I… I'm fine.
- Give him some space.

129
00:11:12,083 --> 00:11:15,041
- Water. Someone get him some water.
- Do we help him?

130
00:11:15,125 --> 00:11:16,416
Give him some water!

131
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:20,166
- How many? How many do you take?
- One.

132
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,250
Here.

133
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:25,375
- Oh my God!
- Drink this.

134
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,625
What should we do?

135
00:11:28,416 --> 00:11:31,250
- What's wrong? Are you okay?
- Nothing.

136
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:34,416
That was so scary.

137
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:51,000
IN A MEETING
PLEASE DO NOT DISTURB

138
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:52,083
Hi, sir.

139
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:55,750
Sir.

140
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:57,166
Uh… Sir?

141
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,208
Excuse me.

142
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:03,000
Excuse… Excuse me.

143
00:12:03,083 --> 00:12:09,125
Sir, this is the retrieval request
for Pin-hsuan's contacts. Take a look.

144
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:12,500
- It's possible that--
- Who is Pin-hsuan?

145
00:12:12,583 --> 00:12:15,208
I observed her
at the crime scene of the man who drowned.

146
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:18,166
I found her very suspicious.
I'd like to investigate.

147
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,416
You'd be better off
investigating the whereabouts

148
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:21,708
of the victim before he died.

149
00:12:21,791 --> 00:12:24,208
Yes, sir. But…

150
00:12:27,458 --> 00:12:29,916
Her cake shop.
It's very far from the crime scene.

151
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,708
Don't you think that's strange?

152
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:36,666
I won't sign it without more evidence.

153
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:45,791
I'm okay. Thanks.

154
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:08,041
CONTACT RECORDS RETRIEVAL REQUEST
RETRIEVAL SUBJECT: LIU YEN-HUA

155
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:20,875
I want to report a missing person.

156
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:22,791
LI HSIN-PING

157
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:25,708
- Okay. Miss, can you…
- Please let me explain it clearly.

158
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:27,666
My friend has gone missing.

159
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,625
It's already been five days now.

160
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:32,958
- Miss, calm down. Calm down.
- Please find her. I've called her mom.

161
00:13:33,041 --> 00:13:35,958
She hasn't heard anything either.
I called her over ten times yesterday.

162
00:13:36,041 --> 00:13:38,583
Miss, can you calm down first?
Let me get your details.

163
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:40,541
Her boyfriend used to beat her, you know?

164
00:13:40,625 --> 00:13:42,708
We have a certain procedure
in these matters.

165
00:13:42,791 --> 00:13:45,416
I'm worried about her.
What if she's not okay? What if she's…

166
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:59,458
We had a good relationship.
We were preparing to get married.

167
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:01,916
But she suddenly disappeared.

168
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,333
I'm guessing she got cold feet.

169
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:07,625
I've tried calling her.

170
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:10,833
Have you contacted her family or friends?

171
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:14,916
Uh… No.

172
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,500
- Uh, but she had depression.
- Depression.

173
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:19,958
I'm worried about her.

174
00:14:22,166 --> 00:14:24,458
Sir, why didn't you ask him to let us in

175
00:14:24,541 --> 00:14:26,166
so we could check out his place?

176
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:29,458
We don't have a search warrant.
Do you wanna get sued?

177
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,375
We could apply for a search warrant.

178
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:40,833
Go and request it yourself
if you think it's that easy.

179
00:15:18,541 --> 00:15:20,458
Miss? You're in a big hurry?

180
00:15:20,541 --> 00:15:22,458
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

181
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:24,083
Did I do something?

182
00:15:34,208 --> 00:15:36,708
YEH PIN-HSUAN

183
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:38,708
RETRIEVAL SUBJECT: LIU YEN-HUA

184
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:42,375
RETRIEVAL SUBJECT: YEH PIN-HSUAN

185
00:15:42,458 --> 00:15:44,291
- He just fell over.
- Hey. Are you okay?

186
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:45,916
Do we need to go to the hospital?

187
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:48,291
Oh my God.

188
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:49,875
Hey! Back up.

189
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:00,958
I bought it at the Calm Toy Store.

190
00:16:01,041 --> 00:16:02,500
What store?

191
00:16:03,083 --> 00:16:04,875
Calm Toy Store.

192
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:06,916
Do they also sell masks?

193
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:13,208
They do, but… the killer
might not be necessarily wearing a mask.

194
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:16,166
How so?

195
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:19,708
Well, anyone can be the killer.

196
00:16:34,375 --> 00:16:35,375
WITCH BABA

197
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:40,833
<i>Hello, guys! I'm Witch Baba.</i>

198
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:45,833
<i>Yesterday, I predicted</i>
<i>that someone would die from drowning.</i>

199
00:16:45,916 --> 00:16:48,750
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

200
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,125
<i>But now,</i>

201
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,875
<i>it's time for the next prediction.</i>

202
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:58,750
<i>Reversed Obelisk.</i>

203
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:01,250
<i>Orient Express.</i>

204
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,625
<i>Reversed Amazonia.</i>

205
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:05,666
<i>In the future,</i>

206
00:17:06,791 --> 00:17:09,666
<i>someone will be stabbed to death.</i>

207
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:24,916
What's up?

208
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,416
Yo, yo.

209
00:17:43,791 --> 00:17:47,750
Everything is fake on the internet.
Anyone could be Witch Baba.

210
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:55,083
<i>So the police</i>
<i>can't read my facial expressions.</i>

211
00:17:55,583 --> 00:17:57,166
Hmm. Thank you.

212
00:17:58,458 --> 00:18:00,375
- Hmm.
- Hey.

213
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:01,541
Dude.

214
00:18:02,708 --> 00:18:03,750
- Oh, shit.
- Hey!

215
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,958
- "Calm Toy Store."
- Yeah. Uh…

216
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:10,250
- Hey! Wait!
- What about…

217
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:12,833
But… all these?

218
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:19,291
CLOSED

219
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:22,916
You really don't know who Witch Baba is?

220
00:18:29,541 --> 00:18:32,916
Hey. Think about it. You must know.

221
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:36,583
She mentioned you, personally.

222
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:42,500
Out of my three best friends,
one's in hospital and one's dead,

223
00:18:42,583 --> 00:18:44,833
and you're here eating a sausage?

224
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,166
What?

225
00:18:57,166 --> 00:18:58,416
I'm free?

226
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,916
Mmm.

227
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:09,458
- Your friend, he's out of danger.
- Huh?

228
00:19:10,708 --> 00:19:11,833
Serious?

229
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,166
News just in.

230
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,416
A-HUA
WEI MENG-YEN IS OUT OF DANGER

231
00:19:23,125 --> 00:19:24,541
Yes!

232
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:33,375
HAVE A GOOD EVENING

233
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,250
- Your daughter?
- Hmm?

234
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,333
You use boomer memes.

235
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:45,416
No one sends those.

236
00:19:48,583 --> 00:19:50,875
"Boomer memes." What are they?

237
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,208
The one you sent.

238
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:55,333
Boomers aren't allowed to send a message?

239
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,375
Okay, boomer. We use GIFs now.

240
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:03,708
GIFs. All right.

241
00:20:07,166 --> 00:20:08,166
I'll teach you.

242
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:13,458
Hmm.

243
00:20:17,708 --> 00:20:20,458
Wow. You don't have any at all.

244
00:20:20,541 --> 00:20:22,166
Let me install this app.

245
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,041
What's Up Yo! Yo!

246
00:20:25,125 --> 00:20:27,000
It's pretty ugly.

247
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:29,583
It's not ugly. You're ugly. Look.

248
00:20:30,958 --> 00:20:32,666
What's Up Yo! Yo!

249
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:35,666
I've designed these myself.

250
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,958
What's Up Yo! Yo! Like this.

251
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:39,916
You need to get your shoulder into it.

252
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,208
Yo! Yo!

253
00:20:42,916 --> 00:20:44,416
Hmm? Eh?

254
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,500
I'll add you.

255
00:20:58,916 --> 00:21:00,458
I have a question.

256
00:21:01,625 --> 00:21:07,708
How do you, on Facebook,
add someone as a friend?

257
00:21:07,791 --> 00:21:09,833
Facebook? Yeah?

258
00:21:09,916 --> 00:21:12,125
Only friends can see
your profile and posts.

259
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:17,208
But I'm different. An influencer.
I get thousands of likes on random posts.

260
00:21:18,625 --> 00:21:21,416
I just wanna know how you add a friend.

261
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:25,083
Yeah. But first, you need a profile.

262
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:31,458
I got you.

263
00:21:35,416 --> 00:21:39,041
Seems weird.
Are you not close with your daughter?

264
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:44,166
You close to <i>your </i>parents?

265
00:21:48,625 --> 00:21:49,791
Don't have any.

266
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:56,208
Dad's dead. Mom left me.

267
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:03,916
Who raised you?

268
00:22:07,958 --> 00:22:11,250
Grandma. Before I left home.

269
00:22:15,416 --> 00:22:17,500
Who looks after you? How do you eat?

270
00:22:21,250 --> 00:22:22,583
Uber Eats.

271
00:22:23,458 --> 00:22:25,291
You think I'm a kid?

272
00:22:33,208 --> 00:22:34,791
I'm setting your PFP.

273
00:22:34,875 --> 00:22:36,541
CHEN YU-CHIEH

274
00:22:36,625 --> 00:22:37,875
Done.

275
00:22:37,958 --> 00:22:40,625
Now we just wait
for your daughter to accept.

276
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:47,041
- Thanks.
- All G.

277
00:22:50,875 --> 00:22:52,875
- You can go now.
- Huh?

278
00:22:56,500 --> 00:23:00,916
You keep them. My daughter
doesn't like me smoking. All right?

279
00:23:02,958 --> 00:23:04,416
- Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

280
00:23:09,416 --> 00:23:10,416
See you.

281
00:23:11,625 --> 00:23:12,625
Hey!

282
00:23:13,375 --> 00:23:14,583
Yo! Yo!

283
00:23:26,083 --> 00:23:27,083
What's up?

284
00:23:27,166 --> 00:23:29,250
<i>Mr. Jen, I've found Witch Baba's location.</i>

285
00:23:30,416 --> 00:23:31,416
Huh?

286
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:33,208
Oh, sorry. What I meant to say is

287
00:23:33,291 --> 00:23:36,166
that I suspect
Witch Baba is Yeh Pin-hsuan.

288
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:39,083
So I went and checked out her IP address.

289
00:23:39,166 --> 00:23:40,750
I know we don't have much evidence, but--

290
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:42,916
- <i>What's the location?</i>
- Huh? Oh…

291
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,625
Hang on. It's an internet café.

292
00:23:45,708 --> 00:23:49,416
<i>"RS Esports." I can text you the address.</i>

293
00:23:56,250 --> 00:23:58,458
CALM TOY STORE

294
00:24:44,791 --> 00:24:46,166
Uh… Excuse me?

295
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:06,208
- Uh… Are you looking for something?
- Oh. I'm a cop.

296
00:25:06,291 --> 00:25:07,958
Oh. Is there an issue?

297
00:25:08,583 --> 00:25:12,000
No problem. I just wanna check
the surveillance cameras.

298
00:25:12,083 --> 00:25:14,791
Uh, the cameras
are all behind the counter.

299
00:25:14,875 --> 00:25:17,791
- So there's no coverage at the rear?
- Only, uh, what you see here.

300
00:25:17,875 --> 00:25:19,916
- Uh, none at the back.
- Why is that?

301
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,875
We're fully compliant. Sir!

302
00:25:22,666 --> 00:25:25,041
That's fine. You can go back to work.

303
00:26:06,916 --> 00:26:08,375
Hey. Sir.

304
00:26:10,166 --> 00:26:11,916
Hey! I'm talking to you.

305
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,000
Hey!

306
00:26:14,583 --> 00:26:15,583
Stop!

307
00:26:55,416 --> 00:26:56,416
Get up.

308
00:27:17,875 --> 00:27:20,291
So, tell me. What were you doing there?

309
00:27:23,916 --> 00:27:25,041
Just gaming.

310
00:27:25,125 --> 00:27:27,541
Why did you run if you were just gaming?

311
00:27:35,875 --> 00:27:39,833
Kuo Ta-fu. Yeah.
Doctor from Hekeng Hospital.

312
00:27:40,583 --> 00:27:41,583
We met.

313
00:27:42,833 --> 00:27:47,000
You treated the shooting victim.
The one with the hemothorax.

314
00:27:47,958 --> 00:27:51,166
So, tell me, doctor,
why were you at the internet café?

315
00:27:51,250 --> 00:27:53,500
I already said. I'm gaming.

316
00:27:53,583 --> 00:27:57,041
You like playing games
like running from the police?

317
00:27:57,125 --> 00:27:59,000
I didn't know he was an officer.

318
00:27:59,083 --> 00:28:02,750
I see. So, you just run
from anyone you see, do you?

319
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:06,333
You play gambling games?
Have many enemies?

320
00:28:06,416 --> 00:28:08,625
Or perhaps you're running
from debt collectors?

321
00:28:09,416 --> 00:28:10,708
I want my lawyer.

322
00:28:10,791 --> 00:28:13,500
Oh. You think you need one?

323
00:28:14,041 --> 00:28:17,666
Why not do yourself a favor?
Tell us what you're hiding.

324
00:28:20,041 --> 00:28:23,333
I suppose you could've gotten away
if Officer Jen wasn't on the ball.

325
00:28:23,416 --> 00:28:25,083
TAKE MEDICINE

326
00:29:06,541 --> 00:29:09,250
- Hello. Sir?
- <i>What did you find?</i>

327
00:29:10,375 --> 00:29:12,708
Uh… Nothing on CCTV.

328
00:29:12,791 --> 00:29:16,833
<i>I checked out his computer.</i>
<i>Nothing unusual in the browsing history.</i>

329
00:29:18,625 --> 00:29:20,416
Hello?

330
00:29:35,083 --> 00:29:37,208
- Wait a minute. Stop there.
- Here you go.

331
00:29:39,875 --> 00:29:43,500
OCTOBER 3RD, 2022

332
00:29:48,250 --> 00:29:50,083
DEATH FROM DROWNING
OCTOBER 3RD, 2022

333
00:29:53,416 --> 00:29:54,541
I knew it.

334
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:05,333
RED HOUSE THEATER

335
00:30:30,916 --> 00:30:33,375
Okay. The Red House it is.

336
00:30:34,416 --> 00:30:37,291
- Can you take a photo of us?
- Let's get one here.

337
00:30:37,375 --> 00:30:39,083
What the hell is this guy doing?

338
00:30:39,166 --> 00:30:40,000
Hey!

339
00:30:40,083 --> 00:30:42,583
- Sir, are you… okay?
- What is he…

340
00:30:42,666 --> 00:30:44,166
Sir? Hey.

341
00:30:44,250 --> 00:30:45,916
Why is he bleeding?!

342
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,708
Sir? Oh… Oh shit. Oh my God.

343
00:30:50,791 --> 00:30:53,583
- Someone call an ambulance!
- Hey. Stay with me.

344
00:30:53,666 --> 00:30:56,666
I need an ambulance
at MRT Station, Exit 6.

345
00:30:56,750 --> 00:30:59,458
Someone's been stabbed!
There's blood everywhere.

346
00:31:00,750 --> 00:31:04,375
So, there must be someone
who can prove your whereabouts.

347
00:31:04,458 --> 00:31:07,125
Someone who can prove
that you were at home.

348
00:31:07,208 --> 00:31:10,541
Or maybe you weren't at home. Am I right?

349
00:31:10,625 --> 00:31:12,166
Hey. Interview room now.

350
00:31:13,250 --> 00:31:14,958
- Okay. Interview room.
- Let's go.

351
00:31:15,041 --> 00:31:16,791
What are you doing?
My lawyer's not here yet.

352
00:31:16,875 --> 00:31:17,875
Mr. Jen.

353
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,375
The news.

354
00:31:20,875 --> 00:31:24,791
<i>It was around 8:00 p.m.</i>
<i>A shocking incident occurred in Ximending.</i>

355
00:31:24,875 --> 00:31:27,208
<i>According to eyewitnesses,</i>

356
00:31:27,291 --> 00:31:30,708
<i>a man with serious injuries</i>
<i>appeared by the Red House.</i>

357
00:31:30,791 --> 00:31:34,916
<i>He immediately fell to the ground</i>
<i>due to the knife wound in his torso.</i>

358
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,750
<i>Local police arrived</i>
<i>at the scene immediately,</i>

359
00:31:36,833 --> 00:31:41,208
<i>however, there is no further information,</i>
<i>as the investigation is still ongoing.</i>

360
00:31:41,291 --> 00:31:45,791
<i>According to eyewitnesses, the victim</i>
<i>is an influencer with the surname Lin.</i>

361
00:31:45,875 --> 00:31:47,375
<i>It has been previously reported</i>

362
00:31:47,458 --> 00:31:50,500
<i>that he made offensive remarks</i>
<i>to people online.</i>

363
00:31:50,583 --> 00:31:54,250
<i>Whether he was killed because of this</i>
<i>is still a matter of speculation.</i>

364
00:31:54,833 --> 00:31:56,041
<i>It also remains unknown</i>

365
00:31:56,125 --> 00:32:00,583
<i>if this is connected to the string</i>
<i>of recent influencer killings.</i>

366
00:32:00,666 --> 00:32:04,708
<i>Will this possibly affect</i>
<i>upcoming events like KOL Stage,</i>

367
00:32:04,791 --> 00:32:09,250
<i>or will the public remain unaffected,</i>
<i>with the events moving forward as planned?</i>

368
00:32:09,333 --> 00:32:12,166
<i>Currently, there are two eyewitnesses</i>
<i>who are working with police.</i>

369
00:32:14,208 --> 00:32:16,250
Can you please describe what you saw?

370
00:32:24,750 --> 00:32:26,250
Okay. Thanks for your help.

371
00:32:26,333 --> 00:32:28,625
He just stumbled over
and then fell to the ground.

372
00:32:28,708 --> 00:32:30,500
- There was blood everywhere.
- Oh. Come through.

373
00:32:32,833 --> 00:32:35,583
Lin Po-lun. 27. Also an influencer.

374
00:32:35,666 --> 00:32:37,041
He was stabbed four times.

375
00:32:37,125 --> 00:32:39,541
He struggled for three minutes
after falling to the ground.

376
00:32:39,625 --> 00:32:41,375
Two citizens tried to help.

377
00:32:42,083 --> 00:32:46,291
Based on initial analysis, the crime scene
was 500 meters down that laneway.

378
00:32:47,291 --> 00:32:49,583
- No eyewitnesses came forward?
- No.

379
00:33:20,916 --> 00:33:21,916
Hsin-ping.

380
00:33:24,041 --> 00:33:25,083
Check there.

381
00:33:31,083 --> 00:33:35,625
<i>This series of events was predicted</i>
<i>by an online psychic influencer</i>

382
00:33:35,708 --> 00:33:37,333
<i>who remains anonymous.</i>

383
00:33:37,416 --> 00:33:39,416
<i>However, we do know that she wears a mask,</i>

384
00:33:39,500 --> 00:33:42,083
<i>and the show is conducted</i>
<i>by drawing cards.</i>

385
00:33:42,166 --> 00:33:47,083
<i>She has successfully predicted</i>
<i>earthquakes and even building fires.</i>

386
00:33:47,166 --> 00:33:50,083
<i>Whether this case</i>
<i>has anything to do with her or not</i>

387
00:33:50,166 --> 00:33:52,416
<i>is still under investigation.</i>

388
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,041
- A-Hua.
- Mmm?

389
00:34:07,125 --> 00:34:08,583
Why is he here?

390
00:34:08,666 --> 00:34:12,416
Oh. Mr. Jen suspects him
in the influencer case.

391
00:34:13,333 --> 00:34:16,041
But another influencer killing
just happened.

392
00:34:17,333 --> 00:34:19,625
Yes. But Mr. Jen, he said…

393
00:34:19,708 --> 00:34:24,500
The killing happened while this man
was detained. That's a pretty good alibi.

394
00:34:25,958 --> 00:34:29,875
He's an emergency doctor.
It'll be difficult to hold him too long.

395
00:34:32,541 --> 00:34:34,708
I understand, but Mr. Jen…

396
00:34:36,625 --> 00:34:39,083
He's in enough strife already.

397
00:34:39,166 --> 00:34:42,166
This could easily make matters
even worse for him.

398
00:34:42,250 --> 00:34:44,666
We need to handle this very carefully.

399
00:34:48,208 --> 00:34:49,250
Release him.

400
00:34:49,833 --> 00:34:51,583
It's my decision. Mm-hmm?

401
00:35:04,500 --> 00:35:08,625
Whoa. He walked a long way
after being stabbed.

402
00:35:08,708 --> 00:35:13,083
Back there, where the body is,
wasn't the primary crime scene.

403
00:35:14,666 --> 00:35:15,666
Yeah.

404
00:35:37,666 --> 00:35:39,625
This gun. Where did you get it?

405
00:35:39,708 --> 00:35:42,083
Oh. I applied for it,
now that I'm in the field.

406
00:35:42,166 --> 00:35:43,416
- Okay.
- Hmm?

407
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:45,791
- Put it down.
- Oh, okay.

408
00:35:45,875 --> 00:35:48,291
Have you forgotten all your training?

409
00:35:54,458 --> 00:35:56,375
First, don't be afraid of guns.

410
00:35:56,958 --> 00:35:58,750
For example, if the target's in front…

411
00:35:58,833 --> 00:36:00,041
- Mmm.
- Okay?

412
00:36:00,125 --> 00:36:01,708
Relax. Relax.

413
00:36:01,791 --> 00:36:03,625
Now, ready. And aim.

414
00:36:04,250 --> 00:36:05,291
Good.

415
00:36:05,375 --> 00:36:07,708
Your legs. One in front.

416
00:36:07,791 --> 00:36:10,250
Relax your arms now.
Keep them very straight.

417
00:36:10,333 --> 00:36:11,333
Mmm.

418
00:36:12,583 --> 00:36:15,041
Mm-hmm? Right. You got it.

419
00:36:15,916 --> 00:36:18,250
Now, give the gun back. Tomorrow.

420
00:36:19,125 --> 00:36:20,125
Huh?

421
00:36:20,833 --> 00:36:23,541
Hey. Wha… What do you mean? No way.

422
00:36:27,583 --> 00:36:31,375
I'm not afraid of guns.
My shooting test score was 95.

423
00:36:32,875 --> 00:36:35,708
Have you ever shot someone?
Shot them dead?

424
00:36:37,083 --> 00:36:39,708
No. I've never done that.

425
00:36:46,291 --> 00:36:48,958
Looks like this could be
the primary crime scene.

426
00:36:53,291 --> 00:36:55,666
There's nowhere to hide or lie in wait.

427
00:36:56,208 --> 00:37:01,291
It's possible the killer
and the deceased knew each other.

428
00:37:06,458 --> 00:37:09,625
Huh. And he was wearing slippers.

429
00:37:10,250 --> 00:37:13,041
- Could he live nearby?
- Mm-hmm. Came down for a smoke.

430
00:37:22,625 --> 00:37:24,666
This was an impulsive killing.

431
00:37:25,458 --> 00:37:28,333
The weapon was bought nearby.

432
00:37:30,916 --> 00:37:33,291
How do you know
that it didn't come from home?

433
00:37:34,125 --> 00:37:36,416
You didn't look carefully at the corpse.

434
00:37:48,458 --> 00:37:51,583
I heard about you
when I was at the academy.

435
00:37:52,250 --> 00:37:58,375
Uh, they said you solved
a serial murder case. Awesome.

436
00:37:59,125 --> 00:38:01,958
I hope I can learn all that you know.

437
00:38:02,583 --> 00:38:04,666
You're learning how to suck up.

438
00:38:09,083 --> 00:38:10,625
Which unit were you from?

439
00:38:12,333 --> 00:38:15,041
I used to work
as a clerk in a police station.

440
00:38:15,125 --> 00:38:17,833
This High-Tech Crime Unit
has tripled my workload.

441
00:38:20,375 --> 00:38:23,750
My dad complained
he only got to see me once a week.

442
00:38:23,833 --> 00:38:28,083
After that, it was even less.
Like, every three months.

443
00:38:28,166 --> 00:38:31,625
- Then, later on, it became…
- Later on, it was once a year.

444
00:38:31,708 --> 00:38:34,208
Until you never went home.

445
00:38:35,083 --> 00:38:38,500
It began to impact your health.

446
00:38:39,291 --> 00:38:42,333
You never really knew
your wife and family.

447
00:38:43,041 --> 00:38:45,125
Till in the end, you're all alone.

448
00:38:46,083 --> 00:38:47,083
Hmm.

449
00:38:49,875 --> 00:38:50,875
There.

450
00:39:00,791 --> 00:39:02,333
LIFE GOODS

451
00:39:02,416 --> 00:39:04,000
He wasn't that impulsive.

452
00:39:05,333 --> 00:39:06,333
Huh?

453
00:39:13,208 --> 00:39:14,541
The knife's label.

454
00:39:16,041 --> 00:39:18,083
LIFE GOODS

455
00:39:25,333 --> 00:39:27,541
- 399.
- Police officers.

456
00:39:27,625 --> 00:39:31,416
We need to see your CCTV.

457
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:32,750
Oh. Okay.

458
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:42,166
Four o'clock, 4:30…

459
00:39:42,250 --> 00:39:45,666
And this is five o'clock.

460
00:39:46,750 --> 00:39:48,416
5:30…

461
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:53,375
And… six o'clock.

462
00:39:53,875 --> 00:39:56,500
- Stop there. Play that.
- Huh? Okay.

463
00:39:59,083 --> 00:40:01,166
Oh! Yeah, yeah, yeah!
That's her! That's her!

464
00:40:05,958 --> 00:40:07,708
<i>Reversed Amazonia.</i>

465
00:40:08,833 --> 00:40:10,166
<i>In the future,</i>

466
00:40:11,333 --> 00:40:14,500
<i>someone will be stabbed to death.</i>

467
00:40:15,833 --> 00:40:17,208
399.

468
00:40:22,625 --> 00:40:23,750
Thank you.

469
00:40:25,208 --> 00:40:26,958
And here's your change.

470
00:40:27,041 --> 00:40:28,583
Huh?

471
00:40:28,666 --> 00:40:30,750
Miss! Oh.

472
00:40:36,250 --> 00:40:37,916
- Witch Baba?
- Huh?

473
00:40:39,833 --> 00:40:41,583
- That the drive?
- Yeah.

474
00:40:44,083 --> 00:40:46,083
- Hey, wait!
- You shouldn't eject a drive like that!

475
00:40:46,166 --> 00:40:47,166
Thank you.

476
00:40:47,250 --> 00:40:48,333
You could corrupt it!

477
00:40:52,083 --> 00:40:53,583
Witch Baba?

478
00:41:10,083 --> 00:41:11,583
KAO PI

479
00:41:18,208 --> 00:41:19,458
- Hey.
- <i>Hey.</i>

480
00:41:19,541 --> 00:41:22,666
- Do you know who was killed?
<i>- Yeah. </i>

481
00:41:23,166 --> 00:41:24,500
<i>Some guy called…</i>

482
00:41:29,083 --> 00:41:32,333
Lin Po-lun? Some random influencer.

483
00:41:32,416 --> 00:41:33,541
WHAT TO DO ON SATURDAY

484
00:41:33,625 --> 00:41:35,625
<i>Wei Meng-yen, go to hell! Let's party!</i>

485
00:41:35,708 --> 00:41:37,500
He dissed Wei Yen in a video.

486
00:41:38,083 --> 00:41:41,625
What does he have to do with this?

487
00:41:41,708 --> 00:41:43,416
<i>Fucked if I know.</i>

488
00:41:44,875 --> 00:41:46,916
Could it just be a coincidence?

489
00:41:50,208 --> 00:41:52,083
I hope that's true.

490
00:41:53,291 --> 00:41:55,125
<i>I'm heading to you now.</i>

491
00:41:55,208 --> 00:41:57,333
Mm-hmm. 'Kay. Bye.

492
00:42:04,833 --> 00:42:06,958
WITCH BABA

493
00:42:08,625 --> 00:42:10,833
<i>Hello, guys! I'm Witch Baba.</i>

494
00:42:10,916 --> 00:42:12,083
AUDIO CALL
CHEN CHIA-JEN

495
00:42:13,500 --> 00:42:17,875
<i>Yesterday, I predicted</i>
<i>that someone would die from drowning.</i>

496
00:42:17,958 --> 00:42:19,500
YUNONG BRIDGE SHOCKING DROWNING INCIDENT

497
00:42:19,583 --> 00:42:21,083
